label: eyepiece
descript: type of lens attached to a variety of optical devices such as telescopes and microscopes; usually the lens that is closest to the eye when someone looks through the device, placed near the focal point of the objective to magnify the image

label: cataract surgery
descript: ocular surgery performed to remove cataracts

label: ocular tonometry
descript: procedure to determine intra ocular pressure

label: ocular physiological phenomena
descript: processes and properties of the eye as a whole or of any of its parts

label: adaptation
descript: response of the eye to light and dark

label: Ocular dominance
descript: The tendency of the brain to prefer visual input from one eye to the other

label: oculomotor apraxia
descript: The absence or defect of controlled, voluntary, and purposeful eye movement

label: eye tumor
descript: any of the forms of eye neoplasm

label: powered exoskeleton
descript: wearable machine meant to enhance a person's strength and mobility
